ENTRY       EC 2.5.1.65                 Enzyme
NAME        O-phosphoserine sulfhydrylase;
            O-phosphoserine(thiol)-lyase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups;
            Transferring alkyl or aryl groups, other than methyl groups (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     O-phospho-L-serine:hydrogen-sulfide 2-amino-2-carboxyethyltransferase
REACTION    O-phospho-L-serine + hydrogen sulfide = L-cysteine + phosphate [RN:R07274]
ALL_REAC    R07274;
            (other) R00897
SUBSTRATE   O-phospho-L-serine [CPD:C01005];
            hydrogen sulfide [CPD:C00283]
PRODUCT     L-cysteine [CPD:C00097];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009]
COMMENT     A pyridoxal-phosphate protein. The enzyme from Aeropyrum pernix acts on both O-phospho-L-serine and O3-acetyl-L-serine, in contrast with EC 2.5.1.47, cysteine synthase, which acts only on O3-acetyl-L-serine.
